Tamil Nadu
Sep 17, 2014
Molestation
Description:
			A cook at the Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF) camp in Agartala in Tripura was arrested by the Government Railway Police at Salem Railway Junction on charges of misbehaving with a college student on board the Thiruvananthapuram Kochuveli-Bangalore Express (Train No 6316) here in the early hours of Tuesday.

The 22-year-old girl was travelling on a reserved coach of the train. R. Ajith, 26, of Thiruvananthapuram, who was returning to duty after Onam festival in his hometown, was also travelling in the same coach. He misbehaved with the girl while she was sleeping. She raised an alarm and the other passengers thrashed him. When the train arrived at the junction at around 3.30 a.m. he was handed over to the police.

Based on the girl's complaint, a case under Section 4 of the Tamil Nadu Prohibition of Harassment of Women Act, 1998, was registered against Ajith. He was arrested and produced in the court and lodged at the Salem Central Prison.
